Oct 30 2009 	What a steal!	I couldn't believe this room when I saw it. We stayed in the deluxe suite which was just slightly more expensive per night than the regular room. It was huge and beautifully decorated and, of course, brand new. There was a full kitchen complete with stove, table and chairs and everything you might need in a kitchen (blender, cutting boards, etc.). We didn't use the kitchen, but if you were staying longer it would be a great place to save some money. There was a sitting area with couches and a flat screen tv, a large bedroom, a huge bathroom with a tiled glass shower and two shower heads, and even a separate second bathroom with the toilet and another shower with a tub (great for the kids, if we had brought them). There was tons of space and everything was very tastefully decorated in art deco. There was even a washer and dryer in the room for longer stays. The fitness center is huge and top notch, and there's a nice indoor pool with a pool bar. Parking was plentiful and free, and it's a 15 minute walk to the strip, or they have a shuttle that runs occasionally (but we just rented a car). We were thrilled to stumble upon this place and get such a great suite for such a small price.	
