ure. We're talking Ikea quality stuff here, folks. The doorknob for the guest bathroom was busted. The cabinet above the fridge was busted and nearly landed on my wife's head when she opened it. The top rack of the dishwasher was busted and did not slide out. The couches were comfy, but they gave off static electricity like crazy- I kept zapping myself all over the place. Ow! And finally- on our last night there, the toilet handle broke. We ended up having to &quot;manually&quot; flush the toilet by pouring buckets of water into it to clear out the bowl. Joy!! All in all, though, I took these experiences with a grain of salt. Had Marvin, the Bellhop (sorry- can't recall his name) and the rest of the staff not been on top of everything, I would have given this place a much more harsh review. Mistakes happen (the key), but they did everything they could to make sure we were happy with our stay. They even gave us a comment card as we left. :-)Yes, I would stay here again- but really- for a brand new hotel to already have it's furnishings falling apart... not cool! They might want to consider investing in some sturdier (possibly not as pretty) stuff.	
