Oct 17 2008 	For the Most Part a Good Place to Stay	We've been owners at Bluegreen for 6 years. Don't even get me started on the timeshare thing...but the fact is, we're stuck with it, so we might at well make the best of it. So when we heard they were opening a new resort in Vegas, we wanted to check it out.We stayed in a 1 bedroom deluxe and it was really a nice unit. The kingsize bed was comfortable and the matress pad and bottom sheet didn't keep coming off like it seems to do in some resorts. That was a plus.There were 2 bathrooms, one contains a counter with a double sink and a huge shower. The shower has 2 showerheads and a bench to sit on...Heavenly! I'm really missing that shower! The 2nd bathroom had a toilet, tub, a counter with one sink and a closet with extra space for lines.The problem though, was that if you opened the door between the 2 bathrooms, it pretty much rendered the 2nd sink useless because it opened up right in front of it. And if you stepped out of the shower at the same time that your husband came through the other bathroom door, you had a near collision because the shower door opened close to the door seperating the bathrooms. That design was poor planning on Bluegreen's part.Another example of poor planning was the situaton with the washer/dryer. They were inside a closet that had no light whatsoever. There wasn't even a light in the hallway outside the closet. We mentioned this to the timeshare salespeople and they said they'd received a lot of complaints about it....but the only way to fix it was to rewire all the units.I suggested they give you a flashlight when you check in. LOLIn spite of these negatives, it's a decent place to stay. It's about a mile from the strip, so renting a car is probably your best option until they get a shuttle going. I was concerned that with the airport being so close it would be noisy, but surprisingly it wasn't. When the planes take off and land, they look like they're flying right into the building- which is a little unnerving at first but soon becomes kind of fascinating to watch.All in all, it was a good place to stay.	
